{:spec/title "Wire up agent invocation in phase interceptors"
 :spec/description "Phase interceptors are currently stubs that only record metadata. Need to invoke agents and get real work done.

Current problem:
- Phase interceptors (plan.clj, implement.clj, etc.) have stub :enter functions
- They set :phase/started-at but never call agent.invoke()
- Result: workflows complete instantly with 0ms, 0 tokens

Required changes for each phase (plan, implement, verify, review, release):
1. In :enter function, after setting metadata:
   a. Resolve agent from registry using :agent keyword
   b. Create agent invocation context (task, input, gates, budget)
   c. Call (agent/invoke agent context)
   d. Store result in ctx
2. In :leave function:
   a. Extract metrics from agent result
   b. Store artifacts produced by agent
   c. Update phase result with outputs

Reference implementations:
- components/workflow/src/ai/miniforge/workflow/agent_factory.clj:32 (agent invocation)
- components/workflow/src/ai/miniforge/workflow/protocols/impl/phase_executor.clj:85 (agent.invoke call)

Example pattern:
```clojure
(defn- enter-plan [ctx]
  (let [config (get-in ctx [:phase-config])
        agent-kw (:agent config)
        ;; TODO: Resolve agent instance
        ;; TODO: Build invocation context
        ;; TODO: Call (agent/invoke ...)
        result {}] ;; placeholder
    (assoc ctx :phase-result result)))
```

Success criteria:
- Agents are invoked during workflow execution
- LLM calls happen (duration > 0ms, tokens > 0)
- Agent outputs stored in phase results
- All tests pass"

 :spec/intent {:type :feature
          :scope ["components/phase/src/ai/miniforge/phase/plan.clj"
                  "components/phase/src/ai/miniforge/phase/implement.clj"
                  "components/phase/src/ai/miniforge/phase/verify.clj"
                  "components/phase/src/ai/miniforge/phase/review.clj"
                  "components/phase/src/ai/miniforge/phase/release.clj"]}

 :spec/constraints ["use-existing-agent-interface"
               "preserve-interceptor-pattern"
               "track-metrics-properly"
               "handle-errors-gracefully"
               "include-integration-test"]

 :tags [:agents :workflow :migration :critical :task-1]

 :context "Part of interceptor-based workflow migration. Depends on Task #3 (validator) being complete first."}
